r that took him throughout Europe and was instrumental in bringing him to America for the first time. For many of Stravinsky's critics it came to represent all that was wrong with his new style, while for others it pointed the way forward through the past, taking on an important role in the Bach revival of the 1920s. By combining sketch studies, musicological context, and straightforward analyses ofall three movements, the book paints a comprehensive picture of the piece's creation, impact, and structure that will be of interest not only to musicologists and music theorists, but to pianists, conductors, and concert-goers aswell. Donald Traut is associate professor of music theory at the University of Arizona.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aMusic. 7aMUSIC / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aclassical music.  aconcerto.  amusic composition.  amusic history.  amusic studies.  amusic theory.  amusicology.  apiano.  atwentieth century composers.  atwentieth century music.  awind intrsuments.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311143131440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782048480423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782048480/original  a978-3-11-143131-4  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles